3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX calculates TAO/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium between perpetual and spot prices. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while shorts receive payments during negative funding periods. The exchange uses a dampening mechanism to smooth extreme funding spikes, with rates typically ranging from -0.75% to +0.75% per settlement."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TAO","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TAO represents Bittensor's blockchain-based machine learning protocol, attracting both AI sector speculation and institutional interest. The token's mid-tier trading volume on BingX creates funding rate inefficiencies compared to larger exchanges, while its correlation with AI narrative cycles produces predictable funding patterns during market trends."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TAO/USDT funding rates on BingX typically spike positive during AI sector rallies, often exceeding 0.3% per 8-hour period when retail sentiment peaks. During market corrections, funding frequently turns negative as leveraged longs get liquidated and shorts dominate open interest. The pair shows distinctive weekly patterns, with higher funding rates during US trading hours when AI token speculation intensifies. Monthly analysis reveals funding rate correlations with Bittensor network updates and AI partnership announcements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange funding arbitrage works effectively with TAO due to varying liquidity across platforms, with BingX often showing 10-20 basis point differences versus major exchanges. Delta-neutral strategies perform well during high volatility periods when funding rates exceed 0.2% per settlement. Grid trading bots on BingX can capture funding payments while maintaining market-neutral positions through automated hedging. The 8-hour settlement frequency allows for precise timing of position entries before funding collection periods."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TAO's mid-tier liquidity on BingX increases slippage risk during volatile periods, particularly when unwinding large arbitrage positions. The token's sensitivity to AI sector news creates sudden price gaps that can disrupt hedged positions before funding settlements. BingX's lower overall trading volume compared to tier-1 exchanges means funding rates can remain inefficient longer, but also increases counterparty risk. Leverage restrictions and margin requirements may limit position sizing for optimal funding rate capture."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical TAO funding rates on BingX?","answer":"TAO funding rates on BingX typically range from -0.2% to +0.4% per 8-hour period, with higher positive rates during AI sector bullish phases. Extreme events can push rates beyond ±0.75%, particularly during major Bittensor protocol updates or broader AI token rallies."},{"question":"How does BingX's TAO liquidity affect funding arbitrage?","answer":"BingX's moderate TAO liquidity creates both opportunities and risks for funding arbitrage. Lower volume can lead to persistent funding rate inefficiencies versus larger exchanges, but also increases slippage costs when establishing or unwinding positions."},{"question":"When do TAO funding settlements occur on BingX?","answer":"TAO/USDT funding settlements happen every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC on BingX. Positions must be open at settlement time to pay or receive funding, with rates calculated based on the 8-hour time-weighted premium."},{"question":"What makes TAO suitable for funding rate strategies?","answer":"TAO's mid-tier volatility and AI sector correlation create predictable funding patterns, while its presence across multiple exchanges enables cross-platform arbitrage. The token's institutional adoption in AI infrastructure makes it less susceptible to extreme manipulation compared to smaller altcoins."}]}]
